Refreshing a living room in Rajbagh, styling a new flat in Lal Chowk, or planning a bedroom makeover in Bemina — interior decor helps you use space wisely and create a home that feels cohesive and personal. Panun Kaergar connects Srinagar residents with decor consultants for practical, budget-conscious styling support.

## What interior decor services include

- **Space planning** — furniture layout, traffic flow, room function
- **Colour and material advice** — wall colours, curtains, upholstery, flooring accents
- **Furniture selection guidance** — what to buy, what to repurpose, scale and proportion
- **Styling and accessorizing** — rugs, cushions, lighting, wall art, plants
- **Room-by-room makeovers** — living room, bedroom, dining area, home office
- **Pre-renovation consultation** — plan finishes before masonry or painting work begins

Interior decor on Panun Kaergar focuses on advisory and styling support — helping you make decisions and arrange what you already have, rather than full construction projects.

## When to hire an interior decor consultant

- Moving into a new home and unsure how to arrange furniture
- A room feels cluttered or unfinished despite having good pieces
- Preparing for a family event and wanting a polished look
- Combining traditional Kashmiri elements with modern furnishings
- Refreshing a space without a full renovation budget

A few hours with a skilled consultant can save money by avoiding wrong purchases and awkward layouts.

## How to prepare for a decor consultation

- Share photos of the room from multiple angles
- Note room dimensions and existing furniture you plan to keep
- Mention your budget range and any must-have items (prayer space, study corner, children's area)
- List problems — poor lighting, lack of storage, awkward window placement
- Be clear about timeline — quick refresh vs gradual changes over months

Consultants can work with local shops and online options, suggesting pieces that suit Srinagar homes and climate.

## Interior decor vs renovation

**Interior decor** is about layout, aesthetics, and styling. **Renovation** — masonry, tiling, plumbing, electrical — changes the structure or finishes. If your project needs both, book decor consultation early so renovation work aligns with your final vision.

## Budget-friendly decor ideas for Srinagar homes

Rearrange existing furniture before buying new pieces. Use local crafts — papier-mâché, wicker, Kashmiri carpets — as focal points. Layer lighting with floor lamps and warm bulbs instead of relying on a single ceiling fixture. Small changes often transform a room without a large spend.

